channel.title: Can't run MoparScape.. Please Help
channel.description:
I can't make MoparScape run. I got the latest Java (with SDK), I set the paths, tried everything like reinstalling Java and redownloading cache.. I searched the forums and googled around, couldn't find any solution. This is the error:
[img]http://img80.imageshack.us/img80/4504/fagerroraf0.jpg[/img]
This is the full text in the clients console: [code][02:17:41] Starting MoparScape 3.2 [02:17:41] Playing 0-hangar.mid Error: loaderror bobStarting up 20 <------an error here!!------ [02:17:42] [02:17:42] News: Welcome to MoparScape 3.2, the pinnacle of RS2 [02:17:42] News: first generation client editing, with a built [02:17:42] News: in private server, music player capable of playing [02:17:42] News: both midis and mp3s, item/object/npc changer/viewer and [02:17:42] News: much much more. For updates, suggestions, or help [02:17:42] News: please visit the forums at www.moparisthebest.com/smf [02:17:42] News: and post in my thread. Y'all have fun. [02:17:42] News: [02:17:42] News: For online servers, look at the [02:17:42] News: server status list at moparisthebest.com [02:17:42] News: [02:17:42] News: -moparisthebest [02:17:42] Server : 127.0.0.1 [02:17:42] [02:17:42] [02:17:42] Loaded 0 random handlers [02:17:42] # Loading controllers[/code]
I will be sooo thankful if someone can solve this problem.. :rolleyes:
